WEBVTT

00:02.310 --> 00:03.895
[ Professor ]
GOOD NEWS, EVERYONE.

00:03.964 --> 00:06.551
TOMORROW,
YOU'LL BE MAKING A DELIVERY

00:06.620 --> 00:08.619
TO EBOLA 9,
THE VIRUS PLANET.

00:08.689 --> 00:10.000
WHY CAN'T
THEY GO TODAY?

00:10.067 --> 00:12.172
BECAUSE TONIGHT'S
A SPECIAL NIGHT

00:12.240 --> 00:14.413
AND I WANT ALL OF YOU
TO BE ALIVE.

00:14.481 --> 00:17.585
IT'S THE ACADEMY OF INVENTORS
ANNUAL SYMPOSIUM.

00:17.655 --> 00:19.585
WOW, I LOVE SYMPOSIA.

00:19.655 --> 00:22.344
IT'S THE EVENT
OF THE SCIENTIFIC SEASON.

00:22.413 --> 00:24.689
EVERY MEMBER PRESENTS
AN INVENTION

00:24.757 --> 00:27.448
AND THE BEST ONE
WINS THE ACADEMY PRIZE.

00:27.516 --> 00:28.585
SOUNDS BORING.

00:28.655 --> 00:30.792
OH, MY, YES, BUT
NOT THIS YEAR

00:30.861 --> 00:33.896
BECAUSE MY LATEST
INVENTION IS UNBEATABLE.

00:33.965 --> 00:35.344
BEHOLD...

00:35.412 --> 00:37.137
THE DEATH CLOCK.

00:37.206 --> 00:39.240
SIMPLY JAM YOUR
FINGER IN THE HOLE

00:39.310 --> 00:40.862
AND THIS READOUT
TELLS YOU

00:40.930 --> 00:43.274
EXACTLY HOW LONG YOU
HAVE LEFT TO LIVE.

00:43.344 --> 00:44.585
DOES IT REALLY WORK?

00:44.655 --> 00:47.344
WELL, IT'S OCCASIONALLY
OFF BY A FEW SECONDS

00:47.412 --> 00:49.067
WHAT WITH
FREE WILL AND ALL.

00:49.137 --> 00:50.206
SOUNDS LIKE FUN.

00:50.274 --> 00:52.067
HOW LONG DO I
HAVE TO LIVE?

00:52.137 --> 00:53.723
[ Bell Dings ]

00:53.792 --> 00:54.896
[ Whistles ]

00:54.965 --> 00:57.103
OOH, DIBS
ON HIS CD PLAYER!

01:33.723 --> 01:35.310
[ Chattering ]

01:37.310 --> 01:38.793
WHO'S THE
GROSS NERD?

01:38.861 --> 01:41.171
THAT'S ME,
AT THE VERY FIRST SYMPOSIUM.

01:41.240 --> 01:44.206
I'M THE ACADEMY'S
OLDEST LIVING MEMBER, YOU KNOW.

01:44.275 --> 01:46.481
THESE YOUNGSTERS
ALL LOOK UP TO ME.

01:46.551 --> 01:48.000
[ Man ]
WELL, WELL, WELL...

01:48.067 --> 01:50.965
LOOK WHO DECIDED
TO SHOW HIS WRINKLED FACE.

01:51.033 --> 01:53.688
WHY DON'T YOU
JUST LEAVE ME ALONE, WERNSTROM?

01:53.758 --> 01:56.206
FACE IT, FARNSWORTH,
YOU'RE OVER THE HILL.

01:56.275 --> 01:58.896
IT'S TIME TO LEAVE SCIENCE
TO THE 120-YEAR-OLDS.

01:58.965 --> 02:01.240
YOU YOUNG TURKS THINK
YOU KNOW EVERYTHING.

02:01.310 --> 02:02.585
I WAS INVENTING THINGS

02:02.655 --> 02:04.551
WHEN YOU WERE BARELY
TURNING SENILE.

02:04.620 --> 02:05.826
[ Laughs ]

02:05.896 --> 02:09.413
GO HOME BEFORE YOU EMBARRASS
YOURSELF, OLD MAN.

02:09.481 --> 02:11.103
NOW, IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME

02:11.171 --> 02:14.343
I'M GOING TO TAKE A NAP
BEFORE THE CEREMONIES.

02:14.413 --> 02:15.550
WHO'S THAT JERK?

02:15.620 --> 02:17.068
A HUNDRED YEARS AGO

02:17.137 --> 02:21.000
HE WAS MY MOST PROMISING
STUDENT AT MARS UNIVERSITY

02:21.068 --> 02:24.033
BUT THEN,
AFTER ONE FATEFUL POP QUIZ...

02:25.793 --> 02:27.068
"A-MINUS"?

02:27.137 --> 02:29.758
NO ONE GIVES OGDEN WERNSTROM
AN A-MINUS.

02:29.826 --> 02:32.481
I'M SORRY,
BUT PENMANSHIP COUNTS.

02:32.550 --> 02:34.275
I SWEAR I'LL
HAVE MY REVENGE

02:34.343 --> 02:36.343
IF IT TAKES ME
A HUNDRED YEARS.

02:37.620 --> 02:39.103
AND HERE IT IS

02:39.171 --> 02:42.861
SLIGHTLY OVER 99 YEARS LATER
AND STILL NO REVENGE.

02:42.930 --> 02:44.793
I'M ESSENTIALLY
IN THE CLEAR.

02:44.861 --> 02:46.793
[ Chattering ]

02:48.378 --> 02:51.620
I'VE BEEN PERUSING
YOUR FORTIFIED WINE LIST

02:51.688 --> 02:55.171
AND I'VE SELECTED
THE '71 HOBO'S DELIGHT,

02:55.240 --> 03:00.068
THE '57 CHATEAU PART-AY AND
THE '66 THUNDER-SCHEWITZ.

03:00.137 --> 03:02.586
EXQUISITE CHOICES, SIR.

03:02.655 --> 03:05.103
AND MIX THEM
ALL TOGETHER

03:05.171 --> 03:06.516
IN A BIG JUG.

03:06.586 --> 03:09.378
WELCOME TO THIS YEAR'S
ACADEMY SYMPOSIUM.

03:09.448 --> 03:11.171
I'M YOUR HOST, RON POPEIL--

03:11.240 --> 03:14.137
INVENTOR OF MR. MICROPHONE,
THE SPRAY-ON TOUPEE

03:14.205 --> 03:16.068
AND, OF COURSE, THE TECHNOLOGY

03:16.137 --> 03:18.378
TO KEEP HUMAN HEADS ALIVE
IN JARS.

03:21.861 --> 03:23.171
BUT WAIT, THERE'S MORE!

03:23.240 --> 03:25.861
WE'VE GOT A WHOLE LINEUP
OF INVENTORS TONIGHT

03:25.931 --> 03:28.378
STARTING WITH
THAT UP-AND-COMING YOUNG STAR

03:28.448 --> 03:29.793
OGDEN WERNSTROM.

03:31.033 --> 03:32.171
BOO!

03:32.240 --> 03:33.413
MORE WINE!

03:33.481 --> 03:35.758
DISTINGUISHED MEMBERS
OF THE ACADEMY

03:35.826 --> 03:38.378
I PRESENT TO YOU
THE REVERSE SCUBA SUIT.

03:38.448 --> 03:39.481
OBSERVE.

03:39.550 --> 03:40.758
FETCH.

03:40.826 --> 03:42.171
[ Thud ]

03:46.620 --> 03:48.275
[ Sloshing ]

03:52.620 --> 03:53.550
[ Thud ]

03:53.620 --> 03:55.240
NOW SIT.

03:55.310 --> 03:56.550
I SAID, "SIT."

03:56.620 --> 03:57.723
BAD FISH!

03:59.965 --> 04:01.688
[ Applause ]

04:01.758 --> 04:02.688
OH.

04:02.758 --> 04:04.033
DON'T WORRY,
PROFESSOR.

04:04.103 --> 04:06.481
IT'S NO COMPETITION
FOR YOUR DEATH CLOCK.

04:06.550 --> 04:09.481
AND WHAT WILL YOU BE PRESENTING
THIS EVENING, GRANDPA?

04:09.550 --> 04:10.586
LET'S JUST SAY

04:10.655 --> 04:12.586
IT'LL PUT YOU YOUNG
WHIPPERSNAPPERS

04:12.655 --> 04:13.620
IN YOUR PLACE.

04:13.688 --> 04:15.033
I JUST HOPE IT'S NOT AS LAME

04:15.103 --> 04:17.206
AS THAT DEATH CLOCK
YOU PRESENTED LAST YEAR.

04:17.274 --> 04:19.172
EH, "LAST YEAR," YOU SAY?

04:19.240 --> 04:19.826
THAT'S RIGHT.

04:19.896 --> 04:21.206
OH, MY.

04:21.274 --> 04:24.033
DID IT PUT YOU YOUNG
WHIPPERSNAPPERS
IN YOUR PLACE?

04:24.103 --> 04:25.103
HARDLY.

04:25.172 --> 04:27.137
WE LAUGHED
UNTIL OUR TEETH FELL OUT.

04:27.206 --> 04:28.516
COME ALONG, CINNAMON.

04:30.172 --> 04:31.447
OH, DEAR.

04:31.516 --> 04:33.516
I'LL HAVE
TO INVENT SOMETHING NEW

04:33.586 --> 04:35.137
IN THE NEXT TEN MINUTES--

04:35.206 --> 04:37.240
PERHAPS SOME SORT
OF DEATH CLOCK.

04:37.310 --> 04:38.965
UH, PROFESSOR?

04:39.033 --> 04:41.379
[ Jet Engine Revving ]

04:41.447 --> 04:43.206
[ Chopper Blades Whirring ]

04:45.793 --> 04:47.723
[ Murmuring ]

04:49.206 --> 04:51.757
OUR LAST PRESENTATION COMES
FROM OUR OLDEST MEMBER--

04:51.826 --> 04:53.274
PROFESSOR HUBERT FARNSWORTH.

04:53.343 --> 04:54.274
PROFESSOR?

04:54.343 --> 04:55.274
[ Stammering ]

04:55.343 --> 04:56.310
JUST A SECOND.

04:56.379 --> 04:57.654
JUST A SECOND.

04:57.723 --> 04:59.620
PENCILS DOWN,
PRUNE FACE.

04:59.689 --> 05:00.930
[ Grumbles ]

05:02.103 --> 05:03.482
OH, YES, HERE I AM.

05:03.550 --> 05:05.379
OKAY, NOW. HELLO THERE.

05:05.447 --> 05:09.862
NOW, WE ALL KNOW TELESCOPES
ALLOW US TO SEE DISTANT OBJECTS

05:09.930 --> 05:13.137
BUT WHAT IF WE WANT
TO SMELL DISTANT OBJECTS?

05:13.206 --> 05:14.793
WELL, NOW WE CAN,

05:14.862 --> 05:17.413
THANKS TO MY NEW INVENTION--

05:17.481 --> 05:19.137
THE SMELLOSCOPE.

05:19.206 --> 05:21.137
[ Excited Murmuring ]

05:21.206 --> 05:24.826
THE ODOR TRAVELS PAST
THIS COFFEE STAIN HERE

05:24.896 --> 05:28.826
AROUND THE OLIVE PIT AND
INTO THIS CIGAR BURN...

05:28.896 --> 05:31.481
AND THIS APPEARS
TO BE A-A...

05:31.550 --> 05:34.067
DOODLE OF MYSELF
AS A COWBOY.

05:34.137 --> 05:36.067
[ Laughing ]

05:36.137 --> 05:38.723
BUT THE SMELLOSCOPE
IS BRILLIANT, I TELL YOU!

05:38.793 --> 05:42.274
THINK OF THE ASTRONOMICAL ODORS
YOU'LL SMELL, THANKS TO ME!

05:42.343 --> 05:44.240
[ Jeering Laughter ]

05:46.793 --> 05:47.896
OH, MY.

05:47.965 --> 05:51.586
[ Laughing ]

05:51.654 --> 05:55.103
I'VE WAITED A HUNDRED YEARS
FOR THIS, FARNSWORTH.

05:55.172 --> 05:58.586
I GIVE YOUR INVENTION
THE WORST GRADE IMAGINABLE--

05:58.654 --> 06:02.033
AN A-MINUS-MINUS!

06:02.103 --> 06:03.550
[ Laughing ]

06:07.000 --> 06:09.240
AND NOW FOR THE PRESENTATION
OF THE AWARD.

06:09.310 --> 06:10.481
LISTEN, FOLKS

06:10.550 --> 06:12.413
I'M PRACTICALLY GIVING
THIS PRIZE AWAY

06:12.481 --> 06:15.413
TO DR. WERNSTROM
FOR HIS FISH THINGY.

06:15.481 --> 06:17.481
[ Applause ]

06:20.964 --> 06:23.000
[ Sniffles ]

06:24.793 --> 06:26.067
OH.

06:26.137 --> 06:30.826
PERHAPS 149 IS JUST TOO
OLD TO BE A SCIENTIST.

06:30.896 --> 06:31.826
YEP.

06:31.896 --> 06:33.965
NO, PROFESSOR.
DON'T GIVE UP.

06:34.033 --> 06:36.310
THERE WERE PLENTY OF TIMES
IN MY CENTURY

06:36.379 --> 06:39.516
WHEN I WAS GOING TO GIVE UP,
BUT I NEVER DID. NEVER.

06:39.586 --> 06:41.550
HEY, ARE YOU EVEN
LISTENING TO ME?

06:41.620 --> 06:42.689
OH, I GIVE UP.

06:42.757 --> 06:44.723
BY GOD, YOU'RE RIGHT!

06:44.793 --> 06:47.826
I'M GOING TO BUILD
THAT SMELLOSCOPE.

06:49.447 --> 06:51.723
[ Professor ]
EUREKA!

06:51.793 --> 06:54.379
DID YOU BUILD
THE SMELLOSCOPE?

06:54.447 --> 06:57.481
NO. I REMEMBERED
THAT I BUILT ONE LAST YEAR.

06:57.550 --> 06:59.447
GO AHEAD, TRY IT.

06:59.516 --> 07:02.516
YOU'LL FIND
THAT EVERY HEAVENLY BODY HAS

07:02.586 --> 07:04.447
ITS OWN PARTICULAR SCENT.

07:04.516 --> 07:07.240
HERE, I'LL POINT IT AT JUPITER.

07:07.310 --> 07:08.964
[ Grinding ]

07:10.067 --> 07:11.172
[ Sniffing ]

07:11.240 --> 07:12.723
SMELLS LIKE STRAWBERRIES.

07:12.793 --> 07:14.723
EXACTLY.

07:14.793 --> 07:16.550
AND NOW SATURN.

07:16.620 --> 07:17.723
[ Sniffing ]

07:17.793 --> 07:18.896
PINE NEEDLES.

07:18.964 --> 07:20.413
OH, MAN, THIS IS GREAT.

07:20.481 --> 07:22.896
AS LONG AS YOU DON'T MAKE ME
SMELL URANUS.

07:22.964 --> 07:23.896
[ Laughing ]

07:23.964 --> 07:24.896
I DON'T GET IT.

07:24.964 --> 07:26.379
I'M SORRY, FRY

07:26.447 --> 07:29.172
BUT ASTRONOMERS
RENAMED URANUS IN 2620

07:29.240 --> 07:32.240
TO END THAT STUPID JOKE
ONCE AND FOR ALL.

07:32.310 --> 07:34.033
OH. WHAT'S IT CALLED NOW?

07:34.103 --> 07:35.206
URECTUM.

07:35.274 --> 07:36.896
HERE, LET ME LOCATE IT FOR YOU.

07:36.965 --> 07:38.343
HOW ABOUT--
[ Laughs ]

07:38.413 --> 07:41.793
NO, NO, I THINK I'LL
JUST SMELL AROUND
A BIT OVER HERE.

07:41.862 --> 07:42.826
[ Sniffing ]

07:42.896 --> 07:43.826
HMM.

07:43.896 --> 07:45.826
[ Sniffing ]

07:45.896 --> 07:46.826
HMM.

07:46.896 --> 07:48.000
[ Sniffing ]

07:48.067 --> 07:51.310
[ Retching ]

07:51.379 --> 07:52.310
WHAT IS IT?

07:52.379 --> 07:53.310
[ Sniffing ]

07:53.379 --> 07:54.965
OH, JEEZ, OH, MAN!

07:55.033 --> 07:56.343
REMARKABLE!

07:56.413 --> 07:59.896
A STENCH SO FOUL,
IT'S RIGHT OFF THE FUNK-OMETER.

07:59.965 --> 08:02.447
I DARESAY,
FRY MAY HAVE DISCOVERED

08:02.516 --> 08:05.620
THE SMELLIEST OBJECT
IN THE KNOWN UNIVERSE.

08:05.689 --> 08:07.930
OOH! OOH!
NAME IT AFTER ME!

08:08.000 --> 08:09.172
[ Sniffing ]

08:09.240 --> 08:10.862
I THINK IT'S MOVING.

08:10.930 --> 08:15.067
HMM. PERHAPS THE COMPUTER
CAN CALCULATE ITS TRAJECTORY.

08:15.137 --> 08:16.413
MY GOD!

08:16.481 --> 08:19.137
WHATEVER IT IS,
IT'S HEADED STRAIGHT FOR US

08:19.206 --> 08:22.274
WITH ENOUGH FORCE
TO REDUCE THIS ENTIRE CITY

08:22.343 --> 08:23.689
TO A STINKY CRATER!

08:23.757 --> 08:26.240
WE HAVE LESS THAN 72 HOURS.

08:26.310 --> 08:27.757
[ All Gasping ]

08:27.826 --> 08:29.447
WELL, LET'S GET LOOTING.

08:30.793 --> 08:33.000
[ Whistling ]

08:35.861 --> 08:38.895
SO THIS THING'S GOING
TO DESTROY THE WHOLE CITY?

08:38.965 --> 08:40.447
WHAT THE HECK IS IT?

08:42.102 --> 08:43.758
AH, JUST AS I THOUGHT.

08:43.826 --> 08:47.895
THE ANSWER LIES IN THIS MOVIE
I FOUND ON THE INTERNET.

08:47.965 --> 08:50.826
[ Dramatic Music Playing ]

08:50.895 --> 08:53.793
[ Man ]
NEW YORK CITY: THE YEAR 2000.

08:53.861 --> 08:57.136
THE MOST WASTEFUL SOCIETY
IN THE HISTORY OF THE GALAXY

08:57.206 --> 08:59.206
AND IT WAS RUNNING OUT
OF PLACES

08:59.274 --> 09:02.688
TO BURY ITS NEVER-ENDING
OUTPUT OF GARBAGE.

09:02.758 --> 09:04.793
THE LANDFILLS WERE FULL.

09:04.861 --> 09:06.826
NEW JERSEY WAS FULL.

09:06.895 --> 09:09.274
AND SO, UNDER COVER OF DARKNESS

09:09.344 --> 09:12.033
THE CITY PUT ITS GARBAGE
OUT TO SEA

09:12.102 --> 09:14.067
ON THE WORLD'S LARGEST BARGE.

09:14.136 --> 09:16.136
[ Whistling Tune ]

09:18.309 --> 09:22.551
THE REPULSIVE BARGE CIRCLED
THE OCEANS FOR 50 YEARS

09:22.620 --> 09:24.826
BUT NO COUNTRY WOULD
ACCEPT IT--

09:24.895 --> 09:27.102
NOT EVEN
THAT REALLY FILTHY ONE.

09:27.172 --> 09:28.895
YOU KNOW THE ONE I MEAN.

09:28.965 --> 09:32.102
FINALLY, IN 2052, THE CITY
USED ITS MOB CONNECTIONS

09:32.172 --> 09:35.861
TO OBTAIN A ROCKET
AND LAUNCH THE GARBAGE

09:35.931 --> 09:37.586
INTO OUTER SPACE.

09:37.654 --> 09:41.172
SOME EXPERTS CLAIM THE BALL
MIGHT RETURN TO EARTH SOMEDAY

09:41.240 --> 09:43.793
BUT THEIR CONCERNS
WERE DISMISSED

09:43.861 --> 09:45.000
AS DEPRESSING.

09:45.067 --> 09:47.206
WOW, YOU GOT THAT
OFF THE INTERNET?

09:47.274 --> 09:49.586
IN MY DAY, THE INTERNET
WAS ONLY USED

09:49.654 --> 09:51.067
TO DOWNLOAD
PORNOGRAPHY.

09:51.136 --> 09:52.965
ACTUALLY, THAT'S STILL TRUE.

09:53.033 --> 09:55.965
Now that the garbage
is in space, Doctor

09:56.033 --> 09:59.793
perhaps you can help me
with my sexual inhibitions.

09:59.861 --> 10:01.826
With gusto.

10:04.826 --> 10:06.000
AW.

10:06.067 --> 10:07.586
SO THAT'S
THE SITUATION.

10:07.654 --> 10:10.413
DUE TO THE SHORTSIGHTEDNESS
OF OLD NEW YORK

10:10.481 --> 10:12.861
NEW NEW YORK IS GOING
TO BE DESTROYED

10:12.931 --> 10:14.724
BY A GIANT BALL OF GARBAGE.

10:14.793 --> 10:18.344
FRY, WHAT THE HELL
WERE YOU PEOPLE
THINKING BACK THEN?

10:18.413 --> 10:20.654
HOW COULD YOU JUST
THROW YOUR GARBAGE AWAY?

10:20.724 --> 10:22.172
HEY, HEY, GIVE ME A BREAK.

10:22.240 --> 10:23.551
WHAT DO YOU DO WITH IT?

10:23.620 --> 10:25.240
WE RECYCLE EVERYTHING.

10:25.309 --> 10:27.861
ROBOTS ARE MADE
FROM OLD BEER CANS.

10:27.931 --> 10:29.274
YEAH, AND THIS
BEER CAN

10:29.344 --> 10:30.861
IS MADE OUT
OF OLD ROBOTS.

10:30.931 --> 10:32.724
AND THAT SANDWICH
YOU'RE EATING

10:32.793 --> 10:34.965
IS MADE FROM OLD
DISCARDED SANDWICHES.

10:35.033 --> 10:36.758
NOTHING JUST GETS
THROWN AWAY.

10:36.826 --> 10:38.931
THE FUTURE IS DISGUSTING.

10:39.000 --> 10:40.931
TYPICAL 20th-CENTURY
ATTITUDE.

10:41.000 --> 10:42.447
HEY, YOU HAVE NO RIGHT

10:42.517 --> 10:44.481
TO CRITICIZE
THE 20th CENTURY.

10:44.551 --> 10:46.895
WE GAVE THE WORLD
THE LIGHTBULB, THE STEAMBOAT

10:46.965 --> 10:48.206
AND THE COTTON GIN.

10:48.274 --> 10:50.895
THOSE THINGS ARE ALL
FROM THE 19th CENTURY.

10:50.965 --> 10:54.172
YEAH, WELL,
THEY PROBABLY
JUST COPIED US.

10:54.240 --> 10:56.447
PLEASE, THERE'S NO TIME
FOR THIS NOW.

10:56.517 --> 10:57.758
THIS IS AN EMERGENCY.

10:57.826 --> 10:59.551
WE MUST WARN THE MAYOR.

10:59.620 --> 11:01.620
[ Man ]
GARBAGE BALL, HUH?

11:01.688 --> 11:03.344
THAT SOUNDS SERIOUS.

11:03.413 --> 11:05.861
VERY SERIOUS,
MAYOR POOPENMEYER.

11:05.931 --> 11:08.309
I GOT BE SURE THIS ISN'T
ANOTHER SCIENTIFIC FRAUD

11:08.379 --> 11:11.344
LIKE GLOBAL WARMING
OR SECONDHAND SMOKE.

11:11.413 --> 11:13.413
SEND IN MY
SCIENCE ADVISOR.

11:14.586 --> 11:15.654
WERNSTROM!

11:15.724 --> 11:17.067
WELL, WELL, WELL.

11:17.136 --> 11:19.309
COME TO PRESENT YOUR LATEST
NAPKIN, PROFESSOR?

11:19.379 --> 11:22.172
NO, I'M HERE BECAUSE
A GIANT TRASH BALL

11:22.240 --> 11:24.172
IS HEADING
STRAIGHT FOR US.

11:24.240 --> 11:25.826
SMELL FOR YOURSELF.

11:29.826 --> 11:31.447
[ Sniffs ]

11:31.517 --> 11:33.240
HOLY-- GEE!

11:33.309 --> 11:35.172
THAT SMELL COULD
BE ANYTHING--

11:35.240 --> 11:39.033
A FAULTY STENCH COIL, SOME
CHEESE ON THE LENS, WHO KNOWS?

11:39.102 --> 11:42.688
MR. MAYOR, WE JUST GOT THIS
TRANSMISSION FROM NEPTUNE.

11:42.758 --> 11:46.172
[ Man Gagging ]
Giant garbage ball...

11:46.240 --> 11:47.688
passed close by.

11:47.758 --> 11:50.447
Horrible stench!

11:50.517 --> 11:52.309
[ Gagging ]

11:55.102 --> 11:58.240
THE TRANSMISSION
CUTS OUT THERE, SIR.

11:58.309 --> 12:00.136
[ Gagging Continues ]

12:00.206 --> 12:03.586
NO, I GUESS IT KEEPS GOING.

12:03.654 --> 12:06.654
[ Gagging And Retching ]

12:06.724 --> 12:08.033
THERE WE GO.

12:08.102 --> 12:11.033
MY GOD!
THE SENILE OLD MAN IS RIGHT!

12:11.102 --> 12:12.344
DO YOU MEAN
HIM OR ME?

12:12.413 --> 12:13.793
HIM.
OH.

12:17.240 --> 12:19.240
Next: New New York in crisis.

12:19.309 --> 12:20.517
Morbo?

12:20.586 --> 12:21.931
Thanks, human female.

12:22.000 --> 12:23.895
Puny earthlings
were shocked today

12:23.965 --> 12:26.413
to learn that a ball of garbage
will destroy

12:26.481 --> 12:28.517
their pathetic city
of New New York.

12:28.586 --> 12:31.102
Makes me glad we live
here in Los Angeles.

12:31.172 --> 12:32.688
Morbo agrees.

12:32.758 --> 12:35.447
[ Both Laughing ]

12:35.517 --> 12:37.136
[ Leela ]
CAN'T WE JUST

12:37.206 --> 12:38.688
SHOOT A MISSILE AT IT?

12:38.758 --> 12:41.206
WE'VE SIMULATED THAT
ON A SUPERCOMPUTER

12:41.274 --> 12:43.413
BUT THE BALL IS JUST
TOO DAMN GOOEY.

12:43.481 --> 12:45.586
A MISSILE WOULD GO
RIGHT THROUGH IT.

12:45.654 --> 12:46.965
[ Squishing ]

12:47.033 --> 12:50.481
BUT SUPPOSE WE SENT A CREW
TO PLANT AN EXPLOSIVE

12:50.551 --> 12:52.481
PRECISELY ON
THE FAULT LINE

12:52.551 --> 12:54.724
BETWEEN THIS MASS
OF COFFEE GROUNDS

12:54.793 --> 12:57.826
AND THIS DEPOSIT
OF AMERICA ONLINE FLOPPY DISKS.

13:00.067 --> 13:02.136
IN THEORY, IT COULD WORK.

13:02.206 --> 13:03.688
UH, IN THEORY, PERHAPS

13:03.758 --> 13:06.481
BUT YOU'LL NEVER FIND A CREW
WILLING TO TAKE ON A MISSION

13:06.551 --> 13:08.033
SO SUICIDALLY DANGEROUS.

13:10.000 --> 13:11.274
AW, CRAP.

13:11.344 --> 13:13.274
[ Farnsworth ]
NOW YOU'LL ONLY HAVE
ONE CHANCE

13:13.344 --> 13:14.413
TO DESTROY THE BALL.

13:14.481 --> 13:15.826
AFTER THAT

13:15.895 --> 13:18.688
IT WILL BE SO CLOSE TO EARTH
THAT BLOWING IT UP

13:18.758 --> 13:21.758
WOULD CAUSE GARBAGE TO RAIN
OVER THE ENTIRE PLANET

13:21.826 --> 13:23.379
KILLING BILLIONS.

13:23.447 --> 13:24.793
AW, BOO-HOO.

13:24.861 --> 13:27.000
NOW HERE'S THE BOMB
I'VE PREPARED.

13:27.067 --> 13:28.309
ONCE YOU ACTIVATE IT

13:28.379 --> 13:30.551
YOU'LL HAVE 25 MINUTES
TO GET AWAY.

13:30.620 --> 13:31.758
THAT'S ALL? BUT--

13:31.826 --> 13:33.240
NOW, NOW.

13:33.309 --> 13:35.551
THERE'LL BE PLENTY OF TIME
TO DISCUSS YOUR OBJECTIONS

13:35.620 --> 13:36.758
WHEN AND IF YOU RETURN.

13:49.895 --> 13:50.931
ODOR AT MAGNITUDE EIGHT.

13:51.000 --> 13:52.413
[ All Gagging ]

13:52.481 --> 13:53.413
MAGNITUDE 12.

13:53.481 --> 13:54.758
[ Gagging And Retching ]

13:54.826 --> 13:56.481
MAGNITUDE 31.

13:56.551 --> 13:58.000
WE'RE BREAKING UP.

13:58.067 --> 14:00.620
TURN ON THE ANTI-SMELL DEVICE.

14:00.688 --> 14:02.758
[ Hissing ]

14:02.826 --> 14:05.309
[ Fry ]
HMM, SPORTY.

14:07.206 --> 14:08.586
[ Squishing ]

14:08.654 --> 14:10.688
WOW!

14:10.758 --> 14:13.274
[ Leela ]
LOOK AT ALL THIS FILTH.

14:13.344 --> 14:15.000
[ Fry ]
IT'S NOT FILTH.

14:15.067 --> 14:16.654
IT'S A GLORIOUS MONUMENT

14:16.724 --> 14:19.379
TO THE ACHIEVEMENTS
OF THE 20th CENTURY.

14:19.447 --> 14:21.206
LOOK, A REAL BEANIE BABY.

14:21.274 --> 14:23.551
OH, A MR. SPOCK
COLLECTORS' PLATE.

14:23.620 --> 14:24.551
[ Gasps ]

14:24.620 --> 14:26.517
SOME BART SIMPSON DOLLS.

14:28.413 --> 14:30.517
Eat my shorts.

14:30.586 --> 14:32.413
OKAY.

14:32.481 --> 14:34.481
MMM, SHORTS.

14:34.551 --> 14:37.102
FRY, THIS STUFF
WAS GARBAGE WHEN
IT WAS NEW.

14:37.172 --> 14:38.620
LET'S BLOW IT
UP ALREADY.

14:38.688 --> 14:40.136
THIS JUNK ISN'T GARBAGE.

14:40.206 --> 14:41.861
I CAN DIG
IN ANY RANDOM PILE

14:41.931 --> 14:43.481
AND FIND
SOMETHING GREAT.

14:46.274 --> 14:48.136
[ Choking ]

14:52.274 --> 14:53.758
[ Gasping ]

14:53.826 --> 14:55.688
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GET TO WORK.

15:00.136 --> 15:02.826
LET'S SEE.

15:02.895 --> 15:04.688
IF THAT'S HYPODERMIC RIDGE

15:04.758 --> 15:07.000
THEN THE BOMB MUST GO
RIGHT HERE.

15:11.067 --> 15:12.033
GET READY TO RUN.

15:12.102 --> 15:13.379
WE'VE GOT 25 MINUTES.

15:13.447 --> 15:15.724
UH, 15 MINUTES.

15:15.793 --> 15:17.586
FIVE MINUTES.

15:17.654 --> 15:19.481
SIX-H MINUTES?

15:20.551 --> 15:22.517
HMM.

15:22.586 --> 15:24.724
THERE'S YOUR PROBLEM.

15:24.793 --> 15:27.895
THE PROFESSOR PUT
THE COUNTER ON UPSIDE DOWN.

15:27.965 --> 15:29.447
THAT IDIOT.

15:29.517 --> 15:31.274
IT WASN'T SET FOR 25 MINUTES.

15:31.344 --> 15:32.931
IT WAS SET FOR 52 SECONDS.

15:33.000 --> 15:33.931
[ Screaming ]

15:34.000 --> 15:35.379
WE'RE GOING TO DIE!

15:35.447 --> 15:36.688
RIGHT?
RIGHT.

15:36.758 --> 15:38.172
[ Screaming ]

15:43.861 --> 15:46.206
IT'S GOING TO BLOW!

15:46.274 --> 15:48.033
[ Panicked Yelping ]

15:49.136 --> 15:50.172
HEY, WATCH IT!

15:50.240 --> 15:51.758
YOU'LL PUT
SOMEBODY'S EYE OUT!

15:51.826 --> 15:53.654
OKAY, OKAY,
KEEP YOUR SPACE PANTS ON.

15:53.724 --> 15:54.931
I'LL TAKE CARE
OF THIS.

15:58.413 --> 15:59.654
[ Sputtering ]

16:02.826 --> 16:04.102
[ Relieved Sighs ]

16:04.172 --> 16:05.517
WE'RE SAVED.

16:05.586 --> 16:08.517
YEAH, BUT THIS GARBAGE BALL'S
UNSTOPPABLE NOW.

16:08.586 --> 16:10.172
NEW NEW YORK IS DONE FOR.

16:12.447 --> 16:15.724
[ Jeering ]

16:15.793 --> 16:17.517
All in all,
this is one day

16:17.586 --> 16:19.965
Mittens the kitten
won't soon forget.

16:20.033 --> 16:21.379
[ Chuckling ]

16:21.447 --> 16:22.861
[ Chuckling ]

16:22.931 --> 16:24.861
Kittens give
Morbo gas.

16:24.931 --> 16:26.000
In lighter news

16:26.067 --> 16:28.654
the city of New New York is
doomed.

16:28.724 --> 16:32.895
Blame rests with known human
Professor Hubert Farnsworth

16:32.965 --> 16:35.102
and his tiny inferior brain.

16:35.172 --> 16:39.826
OH, HOW COULD I HAVE PUT
THAT BOMB TIMER ON UPSIDE DOWN?

16:39.895 --> 16:41.758
I COULD SWEAR I FOLLOWED

16:41.826 --> 16:43.620
THE MANUAL PRECISELY.

16:43.688 --> 16:46.344
I'M A DRIED-UP HUSK
OF A SCIENTIST.

16:46.413 --> 16:48.067
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT.

16:48.136 --> 16:49.620
NO, IT'S MY FAULT, TOO.

16:49.688 --> 16:51.033
I'M SURE I THREW OUT

16:51.102 --> 16:53.895
MORE THAN MY SHARE
OF THAT TRASH UP THERE.

16:53.965 --> 16:55.551
ALSO, ONE MONTH,
MY TOILET BROKE

16:55.620 --> 16:57.826
AND I JUST WENT
STRAIGHT IN THE GARBAGE CAN.

16:57.895 --> 16:59.379
AW!

16:59.447 --> 17:00.758
LEELA WAS RIGHT.

17:00.826 --> 17:04.240
THE PEOPLE OF
THE 20th CENTURY
WERE IDIOTIC SLOBS.

17:04.309 --> 17:05.586
ESPECIALLY ME.

17:05.654 --> 17:07.413
ENOUGH. YOU ALL
FAILED MISERABLY.

17:07.481 --> 17:09.689
IT'S TIME TO PUT
A REAL SCIENTIST IN CHARGE.

17:11.517 --> 17:12.448
WERNSTROM!

17:12.517 --> 17:13.826
THE VERY SAME.

17:13.895 --> 17:16.240
DR. WERNSTROM, CAN
YOU SAVE MY CITY?

17:16.309 --> 17:18.378
OF COURSE,
BUT IT'LL COST YOU.

17:18.448 --> 17:19.689
FIRST, I'LL NEED TENURE.

17:19.758 --> 17:20.550
DONE.

17:20.619 --> 17:21.826
AND A BIG RESEARCH GRANT.

17:21.895 --> 17:22.586
YOU GOT IT.

17:22.654 --> 17:23.689
ALSO ACCESS TO A LAB

17:23.758 --> 17:25.275
AND FIVE GRADUATE STUDENTS--

17:25.344 --> 17:26.931
AT LEAST THREE OF THEM CHINESE.

17:27.000 --> 17:28.619
ALL RIGHT, DONE.

17:28.689 --> 17:30.481
WHAT'S YOUR PLAN?

17:30.550 --> 17:31.758
WHAT PLAN?

17:31.826 --> 17:33.103
I'M SET FOR LIFE.

17:33.172 --> 17:35.240
AU REVOIR, SUCKERS.

17:35.309 --> 17:36.550
THAT RAT.

17:36.619 --> 17:37.895
DO SOMETHING.

17:37.964 --> 17:40.172
I WISH I COULD,
BUT HE'S GOT TENURE.

17:40.240 --> 17:41.517
[ All Sniffing ]

17:41.586 --> 17:42.826
[ All ]
EWW!

17:48.931 --> 17:52.826
[ Screaming ]

17:52.895 --> 17:54.413
[ Slurping ]

17:56.792 --> 17:58.344
IT'S TIME TO TAKE ACTION.

17:58.413 --> 18:00.689
STEPHANIE,
CANCEL THE MAID FOR TODAY.

18:00.758 --> 18:02.205
HAVE HER COME TOMORROW.

18:02.275 --> 18:03.895
WELL, I'M OUT
OF IDEAS.

18:03.964 --> 18:05.309
ANYONE?

18:05.378 --> 18:06.517
WAIT.

18:06.586 --> 18:08.413
IF WE COULD BUILD AN OBJECT

18:08.481 --> 18:10.034
THE EXACT SIZE, DENSITY

18:10.103 --> 18:12.205
AND CONSISTENCY
OF THE GARBAGE BALL

18:12.275 --> 18:14.517
IT MIGHT JUST KNOCK
THE BALL AWAY

18:14.586 --> 18:16.550
WITHOUT SMASHING
IT TO BITS.

18:16.619 --> 18:18.931
BUT WHERE CAN WE
FIND A SUBSTANCE

18:19.000 --> 18:22.136
THE EXACT DENSITY AND
CONSISTENCY AS GARBAGE?

18:22.205 --> 18:23.550
ALAS, I DON'T KNOW.

18:23.619 --> 18:25.550
UH, WHAT ABOUT GARBAGE?

18:25.619 --> 18:26.895
GOOD LORD!

18:26.964 --> 18:28.586
A SECOND BALL OF GARBAGE.

18:28.654 --> 18:29.964
THAT JUST MIGHT WORK.

18:30.034 --> 18:31.758
BUT GARBAGE
ISN'T SOMETHING

18:31.826 --> 18:34.240
YOU JUST FIND LYING
IN THE STREETS OF MANHATTAN.

18:34.309 --> 18:36.550
THIS CITY'S BEEN GARBAGE-FREE
FOR 500 YEARS.

18:36.619 --> 18:38.481
WELL, THEN IT'S TIME
TO MAKE SOME MORE.

18:38.550 --> 18:39.826
MAKE GARBAGE?

18:39.895 --> 18:41.172
BUT HOW?

18:41.240 --> 18:44.136
STAND BACK AND WATCH THE MASTER.

18:44.205 --> 18:46.413
THIS SLURM CAN--

18:46.481 --> 18:48.000
NOW IT'S GARBAGE.

18:48.067 --> 18:49.000
THESE PAPERS--

18:49.067 --> 18:50.172
GARBAGE.

18:50.240 --> 18:51.481
THIS PICTURE OF YOUR WIFE--

18:51.550 --> 18:53.205
PURE GARBAGE.

18:53.275 --> 18:55.172
NOW YOU TRY IT.

19:00.550 --> 19:03.000
BY GOD, I THINK
THE BOY'S GOT SOMETHING.

19:03.067 --> 19:04.205
COME ON, EVERYONE.

19:04.275 --> 19:06.240
THE FATE OF
THE CITY'S
AT STAKE.

19:06.309 --> 19:07.344
GOOD.

19:07.413 --> 19:08.619
DON'T FINISH
THAT CRULLER.

19:08.689 --> 19:09.619
THROW IT AWAY.

19:09.689 --> 19:10.792
BENDER, DRINK THAT BEER

19:10.862 --> 19:12.448
AND DROP THE BOTTLE
ON THE GROUND.

19:12.517 --> 19:13.826
VERY NICE.

19:13.895 --> 19:15.550
GET THAT ROBOT
SOME MORE BEER.

19:15.619 --> 19:16.654
HMM?

19:16.723 --> 19:17.723
WE'VE TRASHED THIS ROOM

19:17.792 --> 19:18.895
BUT THAT'S JUST A START.

19:18.964 --> 19:20.172
WE'VE GOT TO GET FRY'S

19:20.240 --> 19:21.517
MESSAGE TO THE PEOPLE.

19:21.586 --> 19:24.413
People of New New York

19:24.481 --> 19:26.723
take a lesson
from the 20th century--

19:26.792 --> 19:29.240
stop all this
pain-in-the-ass recycling

19:29.309 --> 19:31.586
and throw your garbage
on the floor.

19:31.654 --> 19:34.758
Go ahead, just chuck it
any old place like I used to.

19:34.826 --> 19:36.586
Your city is counting on you.

19:48.240 --> 19:50.792
[ Farnsworth ]
IF MY CALCULATIONS ARE CORRECT

19:50.862 --> 19:53.895
THIS GARBAGE BALL WILL KNOCK
THE OTHER GARBAGE BALL

19:53.964 --> 19:55.309
DIRECTLY INTO THE SUN.

19:55.378 --> 19:57.586
AND IF MY
CALCULATIONS
ARE CORRECT

19:57.654 --> 19:59.758
WE'RE ALL GOING
TO DIE HORRIBLY.

19:59.826 --> 20:01.103
[ Laughing ]

20:01.172 --> 20:02.792
[ Laughter Subsides ]

20:02.862 --> 20:04.413
ALL RIGHT, PLACES, EVERYONE.

20:04.481 --> 20:05.792
PREPARE FOR LAUNCH.

20:05.862 --> 20:10.309
FIVE, FOUR, THREE, TWO,

20:10.378 --> 20:14.344
THREE, FOUR, FIVE, SIX--

20:14.413 --> 20:16.448
JUST FIRE THE DAMN THING.

20:17.517 --> 20:19.931
[ Fry ]
OOPS.

20:32.550 --> 20:34.448
[ Heart Beating ]

20:35.689 --> 20:38.758
- [ One Heartbeat ]
- [ Drum Beating ]

20:51.034 --> 20:51.931
[ Sniffing ]

20:52.000 --> 20:53.689
BURNING GARBAGE.

20:53.758 --> 20:55.034
IT WORKED!

20:55.103 --> 20:57.964
[ Cheering ]

20:58.034 --> 21:00.619
AND SO, ON BEHALF
OF THE ENTIRE CITY

21:00.689 --> 21:03.172
I THANK YOU,
PROFESSOR FARNSWORTH.

21:03.240 --> 21:05.344
I NOW PRESENT YOU
WITH THE ACADEMY PRIZE

21:05.413 --> 21:07.517
WHICH WE CONFISCATED
FROM DR. WERNSTROM

21:07.586 --> 21:10.103
AFTER IT BECAME APPARENT
THAT HE WAS A JACKASS.

21:10.172 --> 21:11.517
[ Applause ]

21:11.586 --> 21:14.689
YES! IN YOUR FACE,
WERNSTROM!

21:14.758 --> 21:16.103
I'LL GET YOU, FARNSWORTH

21:16.172 --> 21:18.309
EVEN IF IT TAKES ANOTHER
HUNDRED YEARS.

21:18.378 --> 21:19.689
[ Angry Grunts ]

21:19.758 --> 21:23.034
AND, FRY, WE OWE YOU
A TREMENDOUS DEBT AS WELL.

21:23.103 --> 21:26.413
WERE IT NOT FOR
YOUR 20th-CENTURY
GARBAGE-MAKING SKILLS

21:26.481 --> 21:29.309
WE'D ALL BE BURIED
UNDER 20th-CENTURY GARBAGE.

21:29.378 --> 21:31.689
[ Applause ]

21:31.758 --> 21:33.931
SHOULD WE REALLY
BE CELEBRATING?

21:34.000 --> 21:35.689
I MEAN, WHAT IF
THIS SECOND GARBAGE BALL

21:35.758 --> 21:37.448
RETURNS TO EARTH
LIKE THE FIRST ONE DID?

21:37.517 --> 21:38.826
WELL, WHO CARES?

21:38.895 --> 21:41.758
THAT WON'T BE FOR
HUNDREDS OF YEARS.

21:41.826 --> 21:44.550
EXACTLY. IT'S NONE
OF OUR CONCERN.

21:44.619 --> 21:47.067
THAT'S THE 20th-
CENTURY SPIRIT.

21:47.136 --> 21:48.758
[ Cheering ]

21:53.895 --> 21:58.275
♪ WE'LL MEET AGAIN ♪

21:59.550 --> 22:01.964
♪ DON'T KNOW WHERE ♪

22:02.034 --> 22:05.413
♪ I DON'T KNOW WHEN ♪

22:05.481 --> 22:10.689
♪ BUT I KNOW
WE'LL MEET AGAIN ♪

22:10.758 --> 22:14.586
♪ SOME SUNNY DAY ♪

22:17.481 --> 22:23.895
♪ OH, KEEP SMILING THROUGH... ♪
